The issue was a `NullPointerException` in `MultiLineIfElseRule` caused by an if-else statement with an empty `THEN` block (e.g., `if (x) else ...`). In such cases, `node.firstChildNode` is null, causing a crash when accessing `node.firstChildNode.elementType` or `node.firstChildNode.startOffset`.

I fixed the issue by:
1.  Adding a safe call `?.` when checking `node.firstChildNode.elementType` at line 98.
2.  Handling null `node.firstChildNode` when emitting the lint violation (using `node.startOffset` as fallback) at line 113.
3.  Updating the `autocorrect` function to handle the case where `node.firstChildNode` is null (empty block). Instead of replacing the child, it now adds the new block as a child.

I verified the fix by creating a new test file `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MultiLineIfElseRuleTestRepro.kt` which reproduces the crash and asserts that the code is formatted correctly (inserting an empty block `{}`). I also ran existing tests to ensure no regressions.

